'''東方航空980號班機'''是一班由[[巴拉圭|巴拉圭]][[亞松森|亞松森]]經[[玻利維亞|玻利維亞]][[拉巴斯|拉巴斯]]、[[秘鲁|秘鲁]][[利馬|利馬]]、[[厄瓜多尔|厄瓜多尔]][[瓜亞基爾|瓜亞基爾]]、[[巴拿马|巴拿马]][[巴拿馬城|巴拿馬城]]、[[美國|美國]][[迈阿密|迈阿密]]飛往[[芝加哥|芝加哥]]的定期班機。1985年1月1日，該班機飛往拉巴斯時，在{{convert|19600|ft}}的高度撞上[[伊宜馬尼峰|伊宜馬尼峰]]，導致機上19名乘客和10名機組人員全部罹難。

==事發經過==
事發時為夜間，天氣及能見度惡劣。飛機在接近拉巴斯時按UA 320[[空中走廊_(航空)|空中走廊]]向拉巴斯[[甚高频全向信标|VOR]]進近，在距拉巴斯{{convert|55|nmi}}處通過DAKON交匯點，高度為{{convert|25000|ft}}，隨即按指示下降至{{convert|18000|ft}}。飛機後來一度偏離航道。

事發地距離拉巴斯VOR信標{{convert|26|nmi}}，距拉巴斯機場09R跑道{{convert|25|nmi}}。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://aviation-safety.net/database/record.php?id=19850101-0 |title=存档副本 |access-date=2014-07-27 |archive-date=2011-07-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707121034/http://aviation-safety.net/database/record.php?id=19850101-0 |dead-url=no }}</ref>由於事發地海拔極高且無人進入，飛行記錄儀未被尋獲。<ref>[http://rgl.faa.gov/Regulatory_and_Guidance_Library/rgTSO.nsf/0/cc60d6b4c807869586256dc700717e5f/$FILE/totalrpt.doc Investigation of Controlled Flight into Terrain. Descriptions of Flight Paths for Selected Controlled Flight into Terrain (CFIT) Aircraft Accidents, 1985-1997.] {{Wayback|url=http://rgl.faa.gov/Regulatory_and_Guidance_Library/rgTSO.nsf/0/cc60d6b4c807869586256dc700717e5f/$FILE/totalrpt.doc |date=20161228075456 }} by Robert O. Phillips. Federal Aviation Administration, U. S. Department Of Transportation, Project Memorandum
DOT-TSC-FA9D1-99-01, March 1999.</ref>

==殘骸發現==
2006年，有登山者在伊宜馬尼峰發現飛機殘骸，但未發現屍體。當地登山者相信發現冰下的屍體及黑匣子仍需一定時間。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/16/world/americas/16bolivia.html?pagewanted=2&ref=world|title=Melting in Andes Reveals Remains and Wreckage|publisher=International Herald Tribune|author=Simon Romero|date=2011-01-15|access-date=2014-07-27|archive-date=2021-03-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309030456/https://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/16/world/americas/16bolivia.html?pagewanted=2&ref=world|dead-url=no}}</ref>2016年5月，美国的两名登山者在攀爬伊利马尼山时发现另一部分残骸（包括已经解体的[[飛行紀錄儀|飛行紀錄儀]]和一些破损的[[磁带|磁带]]）及部分尸体。<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=https://operationthonapa.com/|title=Operation Thonapa|publisher=|accessdate=2016-06-05|archive-date=2021-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210301192115/https://operationthonapa.com/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2016/06/05/two-massachusetts-men-say-they-have-found-long-lost-black-boxes-bolivia/KEDOi2YEOnsMSYfTK7alGO/story.html|title=Two Massachusetts men say they have found long-lost ‘black boxes’ in Bolivia - The Boston Globe|website=BostonGlobe.com|access-date=2016-06-06|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308034855/https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2016/06/05/two-massachusetts-men-say-they-have-found-long-lost-black-boxes-bolivia/KEDOi2YEOnsMSYfTK7alGO/story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://operationthonapa.com/31-years-later-we-found-the-flight-recorders-786d0f9fde61|title=31 years later, we found the flight recorders|publisher=Operation Thonapa|author=Dan Futrell|date=2016-06-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.outsideonline.com/2126426/what-happened-eastern-airlines-flight-980|title=What Happened to Eastern Airlines Flight 980?|publisher=Outside Online|author=Peter Frick-Wright|date=2016-10-18|access-date=2017-01-13|archive-date=2021-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210331040942/https://www.outsideonline.com/2126426/what-happened-eastern-airlines-flight-980|dead-url=no}}</ref>

